em. For clothing, you’ll typically design a decal using an image editing tool (like Photoshop or GIMP) that matches Roblox’s clothing templates. For accessories, build your 3D model directly in Studio using parts and meshes.\n\n<h3>2. Upload Your Creation to Roblox<\/h3>\n\nOnce your design is ready, you’ll need to upload it to Roblox:\n\n- For clothing (shirts, pants, t-shirts), go to the **Create** section on the Roblox website.\n- Select **Shirts**, **Pants**, or **T-Shirts** and upload your decal image.\n- For accessories, you must upload your model as a package via Roblox Studio and submit it for review to be added to your inventory.\n\n<h3>3. Purchase or Acquire Your Item<\/h3>\n\nDepending on your account and the item type, you may need to purchase the item with Robux or get it for free if it’s your own creation. Sometimes, items you upload yourself are automatically added to your inventory under the “My Creations” tab.\n\n<h3>4. Equip the Item on Your Avatar<\/h3>\n\nNow comes the fun part: wearing your creation.\n\n- Head to the **Avatar** section on the Roblox website.\n- Browse your inventory and locate the item you uploaded.\n- Click on the item to equip it. Your avatar will instantly update with the new clothing or accessory.\n- For accessories, ensure that the item is properly rigged and attached to the correct body part to avoid weird positioning.\n\n<h2>Tips for Making Your Custom Items Look Great When Worn<\/h2>\n\nCreating an item is one thing, but making sure it looks good when worn on an avatar is another challenge. Here are some tips to help your designs shine.\n\n<h3>Use Official Templates and Size Guides<\/h3>\n\nRoblox provides official templates for shirts and pants. Using these ensures your textures align perfectly on the avatar’s body without stretching or clipping. For accessories, study the avatar’s rigging and bone structure to position your model correctly.\n\n<h3>Test Your Items in Different Lighting and Games<\/h3>\n\nSometimes, your